<paragraph id="F9F65C8095FC4D6B79D3E41856E21D8E" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
<taxonomicName id="EA1CC08B8988A4FB79A5D63FF52FED04" authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus subsp. var. var. namaquensis" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="sagittatus" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="var." variety="namaquensis">Convolvulus sagittatus Thunb. var. namaquensis</taxonomicName>
Schltr. ex A.Meeuse, Bothalia 6: 682. 1958 [1957]. (
<bibRefCitation id="6EE6FF359A4DC08A8EF6D6078336C270" author="Meeuse, ADL" journalOrPublisher="Bothalia" pageId="207" pageNumber="208" pagination="641 - 792" refId="B225" refString="Meeuse, ADL, 1958 1957. The South African Convolvulaceae. Bothalia 6: 641 - 792" title="The South African Convolvulaceae." volume="6" year="1958">Meeuse 1958</bibRefCitation>
: 682).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2FABBAC1E0D9F6CCF4F60960C05CD562" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="type">
<paragraph id="079CBC4A462F463DEF1C31A4C68CEABD" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="677E5389A00C57F8A425B4AF37C8230A" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
SOUTH AFRICA, Western Cape, 
<emphasis id="1F2A1E6541B6E281EC04070345799A67" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Schlechter</emphasis>
11124 (holotype PRE!; isotypes BM000930470!, K!, P!).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="90F527B6969913FC3CC8DA1368AF63EA" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="description">
<paragraph id="1A5267445349EB2CE11318442FFED513" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2E79A6C555DBF117CE03E5098A0C96CB" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2226B68D22A180F5EA9C8B580F16503E" authorityName="Bernh. ex Krauss, Flora 27 (2): 829. 1844. (Krauss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus bidentatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidentatus">
<emphasis id="C3EEBEE1ACE7666B968A7AC4F63D669F" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus bidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing in little more than the obovate, pubescent sepals, 6-7 mm long, which are abruptly narrowed to an acute to apiculate apex and are not scarious-margined. The peduncles can be up to 5-flowered. Leaves 1.4-4 
<normalizedToken id="3E3A6DB912F696029608C3D5A9750A97" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.5, narrowly ovate-deltoid to oblong in outline, hastate at base but auricles simple, margin sinuate or coarsely crenate; corolla 1.7-2 cm long; ovary conical, glabrous, style divided 5-6 mm above base; stigmas 1 mm, narrowly ellipsoid, sometimes unequal in length as in the isotype at K.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="36434AC2D562E8FF2E854BE0F8D8E98E" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="7376FD7B8616F0F1852A85DF607D4E95" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D8A4788A43C709E581A1A4F27F45370" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
South Africa (Western Cape, especially in the Clanwilliam area) and Namibia centred on Namaqualand (
<emphasis id="440F7D64CDF4ABDFC41D78A5F8B9C4D4" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Le Roux</emphasis>
2836, 
<emphasis id="7B1361179DD1E08FFF007E54FA5E4310" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Hardy &amp; Bayliss</emphasis>
1073, 
<emphasis id="12AD3C87BB4F676926B3F3C38B9C2290" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Hugo</emphasis>
6993, 
<emphasis id="94AC9903DA480C60A057DA705B03B8AB" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Bolus</emphasis>
9424, 
<emphasis id="48111EB83D5A6F5DD003B9A77188D92C" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Dickson</emphasis>
1879, 
<emphasis id="FE52F62F0D87BF687A6A9A72233B9E5A" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Moss</emphasis>
17985, 
<emphasis id="3A8E7D121F928BA8719B0EB544D55271" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Macdonall</emphasis>
18, 
<emphasis id="D7203EC78DD2B6C6467D729C76FA76C9" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Galpin</emphasis>
10544, 
<emphasis id="AA57E8A7E38BD29798D692C4D250722A" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Leipoldt</emphasis>
321).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F3160E675034B2647E504CAC1D964FC" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" type="notes">
<paragraph id="234C3E64E5DCD16D35F2CB26631BFF5A" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF969EFFCD716768895A50875610FA33" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
Molecular studies (
<bibRefCitation id="AD4AC12FDF37484E55E8620D80F00203" author="Williams, BRM" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="214" pageNumber="215" pagination="1287 - 1306" publicationUrl="10.12705/636.9" refId="B388" refString="Williams, BRM, Mitchell, TC, Wood, JRI, Harris, DJ, Scotland, RW, Carine, MA, 2014. Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L. Taxon 63: 1287 - 1306, DOI: 10.12705/636.9" title="Integrating DNA barcode data in a monograph of Convolvulus L." url="10.12705/636.9" volume="63" year="2014">Williams et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) suggest this species is distinct from 
<taxonomicName id="74002F31129FF67F480D607395CF6283" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis id="DD4AD4EAFB71A91161999313EE4476D5" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The shape of the stigmas suggests a relationship with 
<taxonomicName id="551274288082554908162E0BB3A46F75" authorityName="Bernh. ex Krauss, Flora 27 (2): 829. 1844. (Krauss" authorityYear="1844" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus bidentatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bidentatus">
<emphasis id="36DDCA09152B9F78C407DE17A6C6E70E" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus bidentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A3B5FB7B6E2B8C741A9C7D9D22841B46" authorityName="Burm. f., Fl. Ind. (N. L. Burman) Prodr. Fl. Cap. 5. 1768. (Burman" authorityYear="1768" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus capensis" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capensis">
<emphasis id="47F8D077633E8C082E59D099E591BE15" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus capensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, rather than 
<taxonomicName id="C6525D6614F7FB83D227A23FD86BC8CF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis id="1AAD521D7BEB8F2773B5F3442F584098" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9844C0E01C266C52DD90F5931AFA3B7E" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">
We have only cited the isotypes we have seen. The isotype at W appears to represent 
<taxonomicName id="0329CC7EE3EA0DF4F512BD8FEA355000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis id="A1FCC9C1C8C49469C9CAF49A754F59EA" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is possible that not all collections of 
<emphasis id="30E3828020AF822630B42C12F60265AA" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Schlechter</emphasis>
11124 represent 
<taxonomicName id="206ABCDF26EC397B05F880ACA907654C" authorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus namaquensis" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="namaquensis">
<emphasis id="5B4869CCC5E76966458A3E2E67681508" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus namaquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and this may explain why Meeuse treated this as a variety of 
<taxonomicName id="8AE64EACF480425CC5C285F694585D2F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus sagittatus" order="Solanales" pageId="69" pageNumber="70" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sagittatus">
<emphasis id="A0670EB69F0D961915D92F5D4B786BE1" italics="true" pageId="69" pageNumber="70">Convolvulus sagittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
